column2: Johnny Depp...enough said...will not watch another movie from Warner Brothers...You are disgraceful and a liar just like Mira!
column34:
After Johnny Depp lost his libel case against The Sun , Warner Bros. fired him from playing Grindelwald in Fantastic Beasts franchise without caring about the truth or the victim which in this case was Johnny . 
 
They supported and protected Amber Heard which with her own voice admitted abusing him but this was nothing for them so they kept an abuser and fired the victim !

As if this was not enough what they did now has reached the limit not only for Johnny but for all domestic violence survivors! They publicly decided to shame and tease him for being a victim in a musical number in their Animaniacs reboot show ( 1 episode ) !! And by the look of events it is obvious that for them it’s funny to shame victims and call them liars.

It is wrong to let them think that just because they are powerful they can offend REAL victims of abuse , so please everyone let us show them that power can not silence and shame victims !!! Let us show them that without us they are NOTHING!

After Johnny Depp lost his libel case against The Sun , Warner Bros. fired him from playing Grindelwald in Fantastic Beasts franchise without caring about the truth or the victim which in this case was Johnny . 
 
They supported and protected Amber Heard which with her own voice admitted abusing him but this was nothing for them so they kept an abuser and fired the victim !

As if this was not enough what they did now has reached the limit not only for Johnny but for all domestic violence survivors! They publicly decided to shame and tease him for being a victim in a musical number in their Animaniacs reboot show ( 1 episode ) !! And by the look of events it is obvious that for them it’s funny to shame victims and call them liars.

It is wrong to let them think that just because they are powerful they can offend REAL victims of abuse , so please everyone let us show them that power can not silence and shame victims !!! Let us show them that without us they are NOTHING!

column2:
Ms Heard claimed to have donated millions of her divorce settlement to two charities. Subsequent court proceedings indicate that years later they have not received any donations from her. Charities rely on people making good on their pledge so that they can help those that are less fortunate. She pledged $3.5m to each charity, a total of $7m.

- I will no longer support any charity or cause Ms Heard is an ambassador of. (Apologies to the charities but you will need to find more appropriate advocates or ambassadors).

- I will no longer buy or support any product Ms Heard is promoting, paid or otherwise. Including employment in any capacity she has in any aspect within the media, particularly the movie industry.

column2:
I was giving Warner Bros benefit of the doubt with not stating if they are removing Amber Heard until the VA trial but after watching what they did in The Animaniacs reboot episode was disheartening & in poor taste and they are running Aquaman promos on WB and they use a Mera speech for the commercial; it seems intentional & to play Aquaman now with everything going on feels like their way of saying FU.

I am saddened by Warner Bros actions and their way of handling the situation. Our family are HUGE WB fans; from my husband & I watching Animaniacs back in the day (we were looking forward to sharing it & the reboot with our son) to a minimum of over a dozen series we followed over the years on WB to many of their movies too; but we cannot stand by a company that doesn't do their due diligence to research all the evidence proving the actor they are defending is a domestic abuser; the audio with her admitting it alone proves that!

We will never watch The WB channel or go to any movies they release and neither will our friends & their families as we are a large group who goes to the movies together & love all kinds of genres.

Given the fact that this is a Warner Brothers feed I think as sad and tasteless  as this is it doesn't surprise me that they streamed it.  
It is a sad reflection of the lack of moral integrity and intelligence  owned  by those who are responsible for making this type of decision.
What is even sadder is the fact that these individuals would line their pockets and advance their own careers by way of the pain, suffering and injustice caused to others: shame on them.  Karma comes around least they forget.
Stay safe and well.
Namaste

column2: I'm boycotting ALL of Warner Bros. films, TV shows and merchandise from now on! What they have done to Johnny Depp is inexcusable. He is an innocent victim of dv and has been cruelly slander against. The majority of the public is on his side, the massive backlash WB is getting is proof of that. We've listened to the audios, read the court transcripts, seen the evidence and it is clear to all of us that he is the victim. A terrible miscarriage of justice has taken place and it was unfairly wrong of WB to but the blame on Johnny and force him out of Fantastic Beast. Abuse has no gender! We believe him! He has more than enough evidence to prove what he says is true and no bias verdict will change our good opinion of him. Warner Bros has acted cowardly by firing him. But even more shocking, is how they have blantently ignored the concern and outcrys of their paying audiences, when we told them how much we want Johnny Depp back. They ignored a petition of a nearly 1.5 million signatures of real people, who wanted abusive and terrible actress Amber Heard removed from Aquaman 2 after she admitted to hitting JD on tape. Instead of listening to the people who make up their ticket sales, WB choose to dismiss us, mock us and try to silence us by saying we are inflated bots. Well WB, I'm a real person and I'm very much offended by this. I support Johnny Depp wholeheartedly and I will only spend my hard earned money on studios and companies that do the same. If you ignore your audiences, you deserve to lose your audiences.
